gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 152, Spurs 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers scored a franchise record-tying 152 points as they defeated the Spurs, 152-111. Tyrese Haliburton led all scorers with 23 points and eight assists for the Pacers, while Myles Turner added 15 points and 11 rebounds in the victory. Victor Wembanyama tallied 13 points, 10 rebounds, and two blocks for the Spurs in the losing effort. The Pacers improve to 4-3 on the season, while the Spurs fall to 3-4.
